      <div class="prose">
        <p>I'm a frontend developer. I build UI components, layouts, and design systems, and I care deeply about how each one feels in the hand.</p>
        <p>Everything I ship gets time. No vibe coding, no shortcuts. The interfaces I build are the result of layered planning, not first-pass guesses.</p>
        <p>Every feature passes through several layers before it lands. The GitHub issue or project entry frames the work. Private notes hold the messy thinking and trade-offs. The resolution comes back into the issue once it is clear. Only then do I enter plan mode and start writing code.</p>
        <p>What I ship, I'm willing to defend. Privacy-first by default. No trackers, no analytics, no cookies.</p>
